1
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,940
笙ｪOnly after bloom comes fruit笙ｪ

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:28,320
笙ｪWho says glory must fade to the past笙ｪ

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:36,070
笙ｪOnly through thunder
do you reach the clouds笙ｪ

4
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:42,180
笙ｪWho made you the crown of every peak笙ｪ

5
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,990
笙ｪI stand at the center of the stage笙ｪ

6
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:50,060
笙ｪMy shadow is pinned against the wall笙ｪ

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:55,720
笙ｪFacing the light earns every medal笙ｪ

8
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,940
笙ｪLittle birds,
save your needless pecking笙ｪ

9
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:03,220
笙ｪThe open sky rises high笙ｪ

10
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,890
笙ｪWhen night falls,
the moon begins to shine笙ｪ

11
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,920
笙ｪI stand in the heart of these lands笙ｪ

12
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,280
笙ｪMy shadow bears no crown or robe笙ｪ

13
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:22,360
笙ｪThen I know truth needs no disguise笙ｪ

14
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:26,020
笙ｪThe green hills see me as I am笙ｪ

15
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,350
笙ｪLike dew, lightning,
and moon on the river笙ｪ

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:33,790
笙ｪShowing me exactly who I am笙ｪ

17
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,040
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,789
=Episode 47=

19
00:01:38,176 --> 00:01:43,217
笙ｪWest Lake笙ｪ

20
00:01:43,217 --> 00:01:43,977
Wrong.

21
00:01:47,617 --> 00:01:48,977
I don't know what's wrong

22
00:01:50,897 --> 00:01:52,544
or when I'll get it right.

23
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,776
But as long as I keep singing,

24
00:01:56,056 --> 00:01:57,576
wouldn't I get it right one day?

25
00:01:58,455 --> 00:01:59,776
Just keep singing.

26
00:02:06,655 --> 00:02:21,455
笙ｪWest Lake is still the same笙ｪ

27
00:02:24,535 --> 00:02:38,016
- 笙ｪWest Lake笙ｪ
- 笙ｪWest Lake is still the same笙ｪ

28
00:02:42,416 --> 00:02:43,215
How much was it?

29
00:02:43,536 --> 00:02:44,176
Two hundred.

30
00:02:48,056 --> 00:02:49,575
Two hundred yuan for those?

31
00:02:49,575 --> 00:02:51,416
Two yuan each. One hundred of them.

32
00:02:53,295 --> 00:02:55,896
Are you clever, or are you just dumb?

33
00:02:55,896 --> 00:02:57,135
You just spent 200 yuan...

34
00:02:59,375 --> 00:03:01,696
They sell lottery tickets for profit.

35
00:03:01,696 --> 00:03:04,135
It's not that easy to win the jackpot.

36
00:03:04,256 --> 00:03:06,735
And you go there every day
to give them money.

37
00:03:06,735 --> 00:03:08,256
You make money so easily?

38
00:03:08,256 --> 00:03:09,095
Stop nagging.

39
00:03:09,095 --> 00:03:10,575
I'll just make the money back

40
00:03:10,575 --> 00:03:11,375
by selling them.

41
00:03:11,375 --> 00:03:13,375
Who would buy those?
We have a pile over there.

42
00:03:14,336 --> 00:03:15,375
Did Liu Situan come?

43
00:03:16,056 --> 00:03:17,976
Have you no shame?

44
00:03:18,056 --> 00:03:18,696
What's wrong?

45
00:03:19,336 --> 00:03:21,256
He's loaded and generous. Got a problem?

46
00:03:21,256 --> 00:03:23,056
- Aunt Hua.
- You'll milk him dry.

47
00:03:23,872 --> 00:03:24,372
Aunt Hua.

48
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,512
What's wrong?

49
00:03:25,512 --> 00:03:26,816
Aunt taught me to sing opera.

50
00:03:26,952 --> 00:03:28,632
Aunt taught me to sing opera!

51
00:03:29,712 --> 00:03:30,432
How?

52
00:03:30,751 --> 00:03:31,992
She taught me one line.

53
00:03:31,992 --> 00:03:33,592
Then we both froze.

54
00:03:33,592 --> 00:03:35,911
Then she sent me back
because she had things to do.

55
00:03:35,911 --> 00:03:37,191
Any clues where she was going?

56
00:03:37,992 --> 00:03:38,992
Should I look for her?

57
00:03:39,352 --> 00:03:39,992
Take it easy.

58
00:03:40,592 --> 00:03:41,911
Let her take a break.

59
00:03:42,152 --> 00:03:43,712
I'm sure she'll sing again.

60
00:03:44,431 --> 00:03:45,632
It's a good start.

61
00:03:45,912 --> 00:03:48,192
The day has come, after all these years.

62
00:03:49,032 --> 00:03:52,032
You actually have it in you.

63
00:03:53,391 --> 00:03:54,831
Aunt taught me to sing opera.

64
00:03:54,831 --> 00:03:56,551
Does that make me her disciple?

65
00:03:56,991 --> 00:03:58,232
Of course.

66
00:04:00,232 --> 00:04:01,912
Then I have to tell my dad.

67
00:04:02,271 --> 00:04:03,952
Alright, I'll take you there.

68
00:04:03,952 --> 00:04:04,472
Okay.

69
00:04:05,591 --> 00:04:07,551
No wonder I felt lucky today.

70
00:04:07,551 --> 00:04:09,831
I even got a third prize. Shampoo.

71
00:04:11,192 --> 00:04:13,551
Everything is good except for this.

72
00:04:14,591 --> 00:04:15,352
Ribs tonight.

73
00:04:16,111 --> 00:04:17,312
I love ribs.

74
00:04:18,151 --> 00:04:20,472
(Yi Qin'e finally sang.)

75
00:04:21,192 --> 00:04:22,792
(Five years had passed.)

76
00:04:23,111 --> 00:04:26,192
(Her own voice sounded foreign to her.)

77
00:04:27,352 --> 00:04:30,912
(It was as if years of pent-up anger
were lodged in her chest.)

78
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:33,671
(Just like when she took
her trainee class exam,)

79
00:04:34,232 --> 00:04:35,752
(she wanted to scream.)

80
00:04:36,352 --> 00:04:38,232
(To scream out all the bitterness,)

81
00:04:38,472 --> 00:04:42,111
(to give voice to everything
she'd kept buried.)

82
00:05:58,432 --> 00:05:59,151
Uncle.

83
00:06:01,231 --> 00:06:02,512
Once I master Qinqiang opera,

84
00:06:04,432 --> 00:06:06,791
I will sing for my dad right here.

85
00:06:08,072 --> 00:06:08,591
Okay.

86
00:06:20,512 --> 00:06:21,952
Uncle Sanyuan, Aunt Hua.

87
00:06:21,952 --> 00:06:24,233
It's just a meal. Why such a big fuss?

88
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:25,113
So many dishes.

89
00:06:26,632 --> 00:06:27,752
Lobster again?

90
00:06:28,544 --> 00:06:30,113
Aunt Hua, have as much as you want.

91
00:06:30,153 --> 00:06:30,673
You brat.

92
00:06:30,673 --> 00:06:32,113
You can't waste money like that.

93
00:06:32,632 --> 00:06:33,673
Don't do this again.

94
00:06:33,673 --> 00:06:35,353
The nearby barbecue is good enough.

95
00:06:36,072 --> 00:06:36,632
Qin'e.

96
00:06:37,113 --> 00:06:38,153
Hello, Situan.

97
00:06:39,272 --> 00:06:39,913
Hello.

98
00:06:40,432 --> 00:06:41,713
How many flowers are there?

99
00:06:42,952 --> 00:06:44,113
Nine hundred and ninety-nine.

100
00:06:44,673 --> 00:06:46,113
Nine hundred and ninety-nine?

101
00:06:46,353 --> 00:06:47,072
Are they real?

102
00:06:47,872 --> 00:06:48,952
Yeah, smelling great.

103
00:06:48,952 --> 00:06:49,832
Of course they are.

104
00:06:50,713 --> 00:06:52,713
I've never seen
so many flowers in one bunch.

105
00:06:53,432 --> 00:06:55,872
On TV, they only give this
when they're proposing.

106
00:06:56,632 --> 00:06:57,392
Proposing?

107
00:06:58,673 --> 00:06:59,913
Proposing? To whom?

108
00:07:05,392 --> 00:07:07,353
You brat, what are you thinking?

109
00:07:08,233 --> 00:07:09,272
What are you thinking?

110
00:07:10,113 --> 00:07:11,872
I'm afraid it's not just a simple meal.

111
00:07:12,272 --> 00:07:13,913
I didn't come to eat.

112
00:07:13,913 --> 00:07:15,673
I came to clear a few things up.

113
00:07:17,632 --> 00:07:18,432
Situan.

114
00:07:19,713 --> 00:07:21,153
I know what you're thinking.

115
00:07:21,832 --> 00:07:25,033
You've been giving me gifts
since you came back.

116
00:07:25,272 --> 00:07:25,993
Thank you.

117
00:07:26,192 --> 00:07:26,952
It's nothing.

118
00:07:27,192 --> 00:07:28,713
Behind my back?

119
00:07:29,632 --> 00:07:31,033
You brat, what did you give her?

120
00:07:31,272 --> 00:07:34,632
Pig trotters and roast chicken.
You ate them too.

121
00:07:34,872 --> 00:07:36,113
You said they were tasty.

122
00:07:36,312 --> 00:07:38,233
You didn't tell me they were from him.

123
00:07:38,432 --> 00:07:39,553
I'm telling you now.

124
00:07:40,072 --> 00:07:41,192
Please stop trying.

125
00:07:41,713 --> 00:07:43,353
I will never remarry anyone.

126
00:07:43,632 --> 00:07:44,752
What are you thinking?

127
00:07:45,593 --> 00:07:47,392
How could I set you up with him?

128
00:07:48,192 --> 00:07:49,872
How can he possibly deserve you?

129
00:07:49,872 --> 00:07:51,392
Why not?

130
00:07:51,392 --> 00:07:52,272
You tell me.

131
00:07:52,272 --> 00:07:53,353
Easy, Uncle.

132
00:07:54,473 --> 00:07:57,072
Situan, I'm really happy you're back.

133
00:07:57,072 --> 00:07:59,033
But let's stay as fellow apprentices.

134
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:00,993
You don't have to look after me.

135
00:08:01,553 --> 00:08:03,673
Alright, I won't stay for dinner.

136
00:08:03,673 --> 00:08:04,593
Enjoy your meal.

137
00:08:05,593 --> 00:08:06,113
Qin'e.

138
00:08:08,312 --> 00:08:08,952
Step back.

139
00:08:09,932 --> 00:08:11,113
You brat, what are you doing?

140
00:08:12,113 --> 00:08:15,272
I just wanted to treat you to a meal.

141
00:08:15,272 --> 00:08:15,913
But...

142
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:16,872
Forget about it.

143
00:08:17,392 --> 00:08:19,233
It's not happening. Let's go home.

144
00:08:19,632 --> 00:08:20,872
Let's go.

145
00:08:20,872 --> 00:08:22,593
Uncle Sanyuan, Aunt Hua, you...

146
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:24,593
I've ordered so many dishes.

147
00:08:24,593 --> 00:08:25,272
If you leave,

148
00:08:25,392 --> 00:08:26,512
it will all go to waste.

149
00:08:27,793 --> 00:08:30,432
Go home.
Let me straighten things out with him.

150
00:08:34,392 --> 00:08:35,673
You brat.

151
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:38,312
You've gotten really bold, huh?

152
00:08:38,952 --> 00:08:40,473
Inviting us into a trap?

153
00:08:41,452 --> 00:08:41,952
Come on.

154
00:08:41,952 --> 00:08:43,113
You've lost it.

155
00:08:43,473 --> 00:08:44,432
How dare you?

156
00:08:44,952 --> 00:08:46,832
Trying to win Qin'e over?

157
00:08:47,272 --> 00:08:48,192
Why wouldn't I dare?

158
00:08:48,192 --> 00:08:51,632
I'm kind of a big deal in Chang'an now.

159
00:08:51,913 --> 00:08:53,272
Everyone calls me "Mr. Liu".

160
00:08:53,752 --> 00:08:55,752
I've liked Qin'e since back then.

161
00:08:55,752 --> 00:08:56,832
I didn't dare say it.

162
00:08:57,993 --> 00:08:59,993
But now she's hit bottom,
and I'm on my way up.

163
00:09:00,553 --> 00:09:02,673
Aren't we on the same level?

164
00:09:02,952 --> 00:09:04,153
So I thought...

165
00:09:04,952 --> 00:09:07,632
Go take a long, hard look in the mirror.

166
00:09:07,993 --> 00:09:11,233
You pathetic brat.
You'll never find a wife.

167
00:09:11,952 --> 00:09:14,713
What are you talking about? Listen.

168
00:09:14,713 --> 00:09:16,512
Uncle, life is like a play.

169
00:09:17,153 --> 00:09:19,392
People's fortunes shift.

170
00:09:19,553 --> 00:09:20,872
The wheel of fortune turns.

171
00:09:21,272 --> 00:09:22,832
Now it's finally my turn.

172
00:09:23,072 --> 00:09:24,952
You're right. Life is like a play.

173
00:09:26,553 --> 00:09:28,733
You'll always be
a supporting character, got it?

174
00:09:28,993 --> 00:09:30,512
Don't try to take center stage.

175
00:09:30,952 --> 00:09:32,632
Just play your side role.

176
00:09:33,353 --> 00:09:35,353
No, I've got money now.

177
00:09:35,353 --> 00:09:36,872
I will take center stage.

178
00:09:37,153 --> 00:09:39,353
I'll buy out your lousy stall if I want.

179
00:09:39,512 --> 00:09:40,832
I'll buy your whole block.

180
00:09:40,832 --> 00:09:41,872
Then I'll kick you out.

181
00:09:42,072 --> 00:09:43,353
I'll keep Qin'e all to myself.

182
00:09:43,353 --> 00:09:44,553
I'm going to kill you.

183
00:09:45,952 --> 00:09:46,553
Uncle.

184
00:09:46,553 --> 00:09:47,952
I'll kill you brat.

185
00:09:47,952 --> 00:09:49,913
You want to kick me out?

186
00:09:49,913 --> 00:09:51,072
Why are you still

187
00:09:51,072 --> 00:09:52,392
so hot-tempered at this age?

188
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:53,473
So violent.

189
00:09:53,473 --> 00:09:54,553
I'm telling you.

190
00:09:54,553 --> 00:09:56,113
If you dare harass Qin'e again,

191
00:09:56,113 --> 00:09:57,272
I'll beat you to a pulp.

192
00:09:57,272 --> 00:09:58,072
Try me.

193
00:09:58,072 --> 00:10:00,392
I'll kill you brat.

194
00:10:00,752 --> 00:10:01,252
Uncle.

195
00:10:02,353 --> 00:10:04,432
Let's talk. Don't get physical.

196
00:10:04,432 --> 00:10:05,793
Why are you so hot-tempered?

197
00:10:12,713 --> 00:10:13,993
I've always liked Qin'e.

198
00:10:13,993 --> 00:10:14,593
Shut up.

199
00:10:14,944 --> 00:10:16,113
We're not discussing this...

200
00:10:16,113 --> 00:10:16,672
Get lost.

201
00:10:27,473 --> 00:10:29,193
You renovated the place pretty fast.

202
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:31,993
No more opera?

203
00:10:32,152 --> 00:10:33,113
No more.

204
00:10:33,552 --> 00:10:34,672
Opera doesn't pay.

205
00:10:35,073 --> 00:10:37,713
Look, I just set up a lousy speaker.

206
00:10:37,713 --> 00:10:38,833
Everything is solved.

207
00:10:39,912 --> 00:10:41,552
I even saved on labor costs.

208
00:10:42,152 --> 00:10:44,113
Look at the business.

209
00:10:44,512 --> 00:10:45,672
Business is booming.

210
00:10:45,672 --> 00:10:47,193
They need tickets to get in.

211
00:10:48,032 --> 00:10:50,073
Men need tickets. Women don't.

212
00:10:50,593 --> 00:10:51,233
Why?

213
00:10:51,512 --> 00:10:52,272
Why do you think?

214
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:55,193
Otherwise, how'd business be so good?

215
00:11:02,912 --> 00:11:03,713
Where are my drums?

216
00:11:04,272 --> 00:11:05,353
Over there.

217
00:11:05,953 --> 00:11:07,032
Grab them and go.

218
00:11:07,032 --> 00:11:08,193
I have to go. I'm busy.

219
00:11:15,792 --> 00:11:19,233
They left them here? They may break.

220
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:20,193
I'll make them pay.

221
00:11:22,833 --> 00:11:23,392
Drink up.

222
00:11:25,032 --> 00:11:25,792
Impressive!

223
00:11:25,792 --> 00:11:27,152
Come on, fill it up.

224
00:11:27,313 --> 00:11:28,073
- Again.
- One more.

225
00:11:28,672 --> 00:11:29,912
- Two more cups.
- Hurry.

226
00:11:30,552 --> 00:11:31,073
Okay.

227
00:11:31,073 --> 00:11:31,912
Two more cups.

228
00:11:31,912 --> 00:11:33,433
You're the best, sir.

229
00:11:34,073 --> 00:11:34,953
Alright.

230
00:11:36,113 --> 00:11:36,672
Keep going.

231
00:11:36,672 --> 00:11:37,632
I can't drink anymore.

232
00:11:37,632 --> 00:11:38,672
- Two more cups.
- Two more cups.

233
00:11:38,672 --> 00:11:39,473
Alright.

234
00:11:39,473 --> 00:11:40,433
Don't just stand there.

235
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:42,193
- Together.
- Okay.

236
00:11:44,593 --> 00:11:47,233
It's not even dark yet,
and you're already wasted.

237
00:11:47,993 --> 00:11:51,353
Your master will kill you
if he finds out about this.

238
00:11:52,752 --> 00:11:54,833
Although Qin'e doesn't fancy you,

239
00:11:55,552 --> 00:11:57,113
you shouldn't sink so low.

240
00:12:04,433 --> 00:12:05,392
My master?

241
00:12:08,993 --> 00:12:13,032
You've been asking about my master,
haven't you?

242
00:12:14,953 --> 00:12:15,912
Here's what happened.

243
00:12:19,473 --> 00:12:21,353
During those years in Gansu,

244
00:12:22,912 --> 00:12:24,872
we barely had any good days.

245
00:12:27,752 --> 00:12:29,672
People asked him to direct plays,

246
00:12:30,473 --> 00:12:33,392
hoping to get the plays ready
as soon as possible

247
00:12:34,272 --> 00:12:35,313
to make money.

248
00:12:37,632 --> 00:12:38,272
He wouldn't.

249
00:12:39,313 --> 00:12:41,632
He insisted on making art.

250
00:12:43,392 --> 00:12:47,713
He had to make every play perfect,

251
00:12:48,792 --> 00:12:50,353
directing over and over,

252
00:12:50,912 --> 00:12:52,953
polishing every detail.

253
00:12:55,953 --> 00:12:57,512
After all that directing,

254
00:12:59,152 --> 00:13:00,833
he ended up with a three-word comment,

255
00:13:02,392 --> 00:13:03,353
"Not worth it".

256
00:13:05,433 --> 00:13:08,073
As time went by,
he got hired less and less.

257
00:13:08,912 --> 00:13:10,152
In the end,

258
00:13:12,713 --> 00:13:14,392
he got kicked out.

259
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:18,032
(The day they threw him out,
the sun was blazing.)

260
00:13:18,953 --> 00:13:22,593
(When I saw my master
loading luggage onto the tractor,)

261
00:13:24,032 --> 00:13:25,752
(I figured it all out.)

262
00:13:26,792 --> 00:13:27,672
(Performing opera)

263
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:30,073
(is no big deal.)

264
00:13:31,353 --> 00:13:32,752
(It's just a way to get by.)

265
00:13:44,152 --> 00:13:44,752
Let's go.

266
00:13:59,872 --> 00:14:01,512
(In the end, I didn't go with him.)

267
00:14:02,792 --> 00:14:03,593
(Then)

268
00:14:04,912 --> 00:14:06,032
(the tractor overturned.)

269
00:14:32,233 --> 00:14:33,672
Such a simple truth

270
00:14:35,672 --> 00:14:37,473
took me over a decade to grasp.

271
00:14:38,593 --> 00:14:40,392
But he never figured it out.

272
00:14:42,993 --> 00:14:43,993
Is it worth it?

273
00:14:49,512 --> 00:14:50,713
I just don't get it.

274
00:14:51,152 --> 00:14:54,032
Why are you people so stubborn?

275
00:14:54,993 --> 00:14:55,993
My master.

276
00:14:56,912 --> 00:14:57,552
You.

277
00:15:00,713 --> 00:15:01,953
And Qin'e.

278
00:15:03,272 --> 00:15:05,353
What are you after?

279
00:15:05,353 --> 00:15:07,073
What is it all about?

280
00:15:13,152 --> 00:15:14,353
I'm telling you.

281
00:15:15,272 --> 00:15:16,512
From now on,

282
00:15:17,672 --> 00:15:19,632
stop calling Gu "master".

283
00:15:20,353 --> 00:15:22,073
I'm expelling you on his behalf.

284
00:15:22,752 --> 00:15:25,632
Expelling me? On what ground?

285
00:15:26,193 --> 00:15:27,912
Because you're a brat.

286
00:15:29,792 --> 00:15:30,872
Expelling me?

287
00:15:31,713 --> 00:15:33,792
You can't even afford fancy food.

288
00:15:38,313 --> 00:15:38,953
How do I look?

289
00:15:40,152 --> 00:15:40,872
Gorgeous.

290
00:15:47,433 --> 00:15:49,713
Okay, I'll wear this for the exam.

291
00:15:50,152 --> 00:15:51,912
Alright, if you like it.

292
00:15:53,593 --> 00:15:54,593
My dad said

293
00:15:55,512 --> 00:15:58,672
that girls on stage
are the most beautiful.

294
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:02,353
That's why I want to learn opera.

295
00:16:03,552 --> 00:16:05,512
I want him to see me at my best.

296
00:16:06,313 --> 00:16:07,752
Singing opera is tough.

297
00:16:08,512 --> 00:16:09,433
Physically

298
00:16:09,953 --> 00:16:11,152
and mentally.

299
00:16:13,872 --> 00:16:15,193
Are you sure about this?

300
00:16:17,313 --> 00:16:18,353
What isn't tough?

301
00:16:21,353 --> 00:16:22,433
Everything's tough.

302
00:16:23,792 --> 00:16:24,912
So why should I be scared?

303
00:16:31,313 --> 00:16:33,313
Now I've got nothing to do.

304
00:16:36,993 --> 00:16:38,272
You charge one yuan per game.

305
00:16:38,272 --> 00:16:40,313
How long to play off 1000 yuan?

306
00:16:41,193 --> 00:16:43,512
Let him play. It's better than the bar.

307
00:16:44,032 --> 00:16:45,313
It's almost dark.

308
00:16:46,152 --> 00:16:46,872
It went in.

309
00:16:48,552 --> 00:16:49,193
Keep going.

310
00:16:49,993 --> 00:16:51,152
I'll play for you then.

311
00:16:55,433 --> 00:16:56,073
It went in.

312
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:03,752
Look, starting this round.

313
00:17:04,872 --> 00:17:06,993
Raising prices on the spot?

314
00:17:07,313 --> 00:17:08,233
Are you playing or not?

315
00:17:19,872 --> 00:17:20,593
(500 per game)
Sure.

316
00:17:21,193 --> 00:17:22,032
I'm done.

317
00:17:25,392 --> 00:17:26,193
You brat.

318
00:17:30,593 --> 00:17:31,993
How much money do you have

319
00:17:32,593 --> 00:17:33,593
to waste it like this?

320
00:17:34,993 --> 00:17:37,593
I could totally
buy this whole stall of yours.

321
00:17:39,073 --> 00:17:40,993
However much money you have,
it will run out.

322
00:17:42,113 --> 00:17:45,152
How did you manage to make money
with that brain of yours?

323
00:17:46,113 --> 00:17:47,113
I have no idea.

324
00:17:48,872 --> 00:17:50,993
Back when I followed my master,

325
00:17:50,993 --> 00:17:52,872
I did whatever he told me to do.

326
00:17:53,473 --> 00:17:55,032
Then I followed my boss

327
00:17:56,073 --> 00:17:58,313
and did whatever he asked me to do.

328
00:17:58,953 --> 00:18:01,473
Here's something you can do.

329
00:18:02,752 --> 00:18:05,073
Listen. Go to Wenzhou.

330
00:18:06,152 --> 00:18:07,632
Plenty of valve factories there.

331
00:18:08,272 --> 00:18:09,912
Bring some valves to sell here.

332
00:18:10,552 --> 00:18:12,032
Water, gas, three-way valves.

333
00:18:12,552 --> 00:18:13,872
They cost 2000 yuan there.

334
00:18:13,872 --> 00:18:15,672
But you can sell them for 20,000 here.

335
00:18:17,193 --> 00:18:17,792
Really?

336
00:18:18,152 --> 00:18:19,433
Just do as I say.

337
00:18:20,193 --> 00:18:21,953
I've been studying this for ages.

338
00:18:25,193 --> 00:18:25,752
No way.

339
00:18:26,032 --> 00:18:27,073
I'll leave Qin'e here?

340
00:18:27,632 --> 00:18:28,632
You want a beating?

341
00:18:29,512 --> 00:18:30,073
Fine.

342
00:18:30,473 --> 00:18:31,713
Take good care of Qin'e.

343
00:18:31,993 --> 00:18:33,073
Get going.

344
00:18:33,073 --> 00:18:35,593
Don't come back
if you can't figure this out.

345
00:18:36,713 --> 00:18:37,752
Scout it out for me.

346
00:18:38,672 --> 00:18:41,433
Alright then, I'll go to Wenzhou
and check it out for us.

347
00:18:41,832 --> 00:18:43,032
If I make money, we split it.

348
00:18:43,713 --> 00:18:44,433
Sure.

349
00:18:46,032 --> 00:18:46,633
My bag.

350
00:18:47,473 --> 00:18:48,352
Wenzhou.

351
00:18:49,953 --> 00:18:51,193
Such a lucrative job.

352
00:18:52,913 --> 00:18:53,913
Idiot.

353
00:18:54,812 --> 00:18:56,312
Come on, let's wrap it up.

354
00:18:56,792 --> 00:18:58,233
I finally got rid of him.

355
00:18:58,993 --> 00:19:00,193
That fool got something

356
00:19:00,512 --> 00:19:01,752
for nothing.

357
00:19:02,592 --> 00:19:07,776
(Qinqiang Opera Theater New Student Admission Test)
笙ｪGrandma tells of the brave old days笙ｪ

358
00:19:07,776 --> 00:19:16,832
笙ｪWhen sacrifices were made笙ｪ

359
00:19:18,312 --> 00:19:19,993
It's okay. Don't be nervous.

360
00:19:19,993 --> 00:19:20,752
Keep singing.

361
00:19:21,673 --> 00:19:26,993
笙ｪAs it turned out笙ｪ

362
00:19:28,153 --> 00:19:32,592
笙ｪI was笙ｪ

363
00:19:34,393 --> 00:19:35,592
She's not so good.

364
00:19:37,072 --> 00:19:42,832
笙ｪBorn in the wind
and raised in the rain笙ｪ

365
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:45,399
(Independent Enrollment
Registration Office)

366
00:20:00,633 --> 00:20:01,633
Why are you here?

367
00:20:01,633 --> 00:20:02,352
Where's Song Yu?

368
00:20:03,193 --> 00:20:04,312
She's taking the exam.

369
00:20:04,752 --> 00:20:05,752
Why aren't you with her?

370
00:20:06,112 --> 00:20:06,873
It's not allowed.

371
00:20:07,933 --> 00:20:08,433
She...

372
00:20:08,433 --> 00:20:09,953
Yeah, let her take the exam alone.

373
00:20:10,193 --> 00:20:11,112
A little challenge.

374
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:13,473
People would say
that we pulled some strings

375
00:20:13,473 --> 00:20:14,473
if we accompanied her.

376
00:20:16,352 --> 00:20:18,153
Who looked after her during the exam?

377
00:20:18,913 --> 00:20:20,913
No one looked after her during the exam?

378
00:20:21,913 --> 00:20:23,032
You didn't use connections?

379
00:20:23,352 --> 00:20:26,193
You wished you could
take the exam for her.

380
00:20:26,193 --> 00:20:27,233
That never happened.

381
00:20:27,993 --> 00:20:29,193
When did I ever interfere?

382
00:20:29,193 --> 00:20:30,393
She went alone.

383
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:32,312
Yeah, she went alone.

384
00:20:33,312 --> 00:20:35,792
Go get some ribs for the kid.

385
00:20:36,352 --> 00:20:37,433
Let's make rib stew.

386
00:20:38,032 --> 00:20:39,072
Hello, teachers.

387
00:20:39,072 --> 00:20:40,112
My name is Song Yu.

388
00:20:40,112 --> 00:20:41,473
Candidate No. 42.

389
00:20:41,473 --> 00:20:44,433
My selected piece
is from "Duanqiao Bridge".

390
00:20:44,713 --> 00:20:45,433
Duanqiao Bridge?

391
00:20:45,752 --> 00:20:46,592
What's wrong?

392
00:20:46,873 --> 00:20:47,633
Please start.

393
00:20:48,592 --> 00:21:00,393
笙ｪWest Lake is still the same笙ｪ

394
00:21:08,473 --> 00:21:18,552
笙ｪBut my haggard self
can't face this autumn scenery笙ｪ

395
00:21:19,312 --> 00:21:24,452
笙ｪFrost dyes the maple red笙ｪ

396
00:21:24,452 --> 00:21:29,993
(Examiner: Xue Guisheng, Feng Zi)
笙ｪThe cold forest grows thin笙ｪ

397
00:21:30,993 --> 00:21:43,233
笙ｪToo painful to look back
on those past travels笙ｪ

398
00:21:44,953 --> 00:21:46,592
When will they post the results?

399
00:21:47,713 --> 00:21:49,633
I wonder if Song Yu passed the exam.

400
00:21:54,713 --> 00:21:56,233
You should worry about yourself.

401
00:21:56,752 --> 00:21:57,873
What's the date today?

402
00:21:58,393 --> 00:21:58,913
Why?

403
00:21:59,512 --> 00:22:01,512
What about that debt you owe?

404
00:22:11,153 --> 00:22:13,312
Don't run. Come back.

405
00:22:14,312 --> 00:22:15,953
Stop running. Get back here.

406
00:22:16,873 --> 00:22:17,713
Give me the money.

407
00:22:27,272 --> 00:22:27,832
Aunt Hua.

408
00:22:28,272 --> 00:22:28,993
Hi, Situan.

409
00:22:28,993 --> 00:22:29,673
What's wrong?

410
00:22:29,913 --> 00:22:31,032
Watching the commotion.

411
00:22:31,032 --> 00:22:32,233
Comm... Where's my uncle?

412
00:22:32,873 --> 00:22:35,832
Your uncle went to exercise.

413
00:22:35,832 --> 00:22:37,153
He went to exercise?

414
00:22:39,873 --> 00:22:41,792
Stop right there, Hu Sanyuan.

415
00:22:43,233 --> 00:22:45,112
Uncle, why are you running?

416
00:22:45,112 --> 00:22:46,312
Didn't you go to Wenzhou?

417
00:22:46,752 --> 00:22:47,473
Well, I'm back.

418
00:22:47,473 --> 00:22:48,272
Stop running.

419
00:22:51,193 --> 00:22:53,552
Aunt, what's going on here?

420
00:22:54,112 --> 00:22:55,032
A debt collector.

421
00:22:55,552 --> 00:22:56,873
Uncle owes someone money?

422
00:22:56,873 --> 00:22:58,072
I didn't say that.

423
00:23:01,973 --> 00:23:03,673
Uncle, how much do you owe?

424
00:23:03,673 --> 00:23:04,552
Thirty thousand.

425
00:23:04,552 --> 00:23:05,913
Come back.

426
00:23:06,473 --> 00:23:07,993
Stop.

427
00:23:09,072 --> 00:23:10,393
It's only 30,000 yuan.

428
00:23:10,393 --> 00:23:11,592
I thought it was a big deal.

429
00:23:12,072 --> 00:23:12,873
I'll pay it back.

430
00:23:15,473 --> 00:23:16,673
Quit staring. Take it.

431
00:23:31,272 --> 00:23:34,473
Uncle, I settled this for you.

432
00:23:35,713 --> 00:23:37,233
I don't want your money.

433
00:23:37,993 --> 00:23:39,592
I used to owe that guy.

434
00:23:40,233 --> 00:23:41,512
Now I owe you.

435
00:23:43,352 --> 00:23:45,512
Rest assured. I'll pay you back slowly.

436
00:23:46,032 --> 00:23:47,633
You don't have to pay me back.

437
00:23:48,032 --> 00:23:49,433
I'll deduct it from your dividend.

438
00:23:49,993 --> 00:23:50,752
What dividend?

439
00:23:51,312 --> 00:23:51,913
You forgot?

440
00:23:52,433 --> 00:23:54,713
Didn't you tell me
to get valves from Wenzhou?

441
00:23:55,153 --> 00:23:55,993
I got the valves

442
00:23:57,032 --> 00:23:57,913
and made money.

443
00:23:58,832 --> 00:23:59,512
What?

444
00:24:00,393 --> 00:24:01,072
You made money?

445
00:24:09,233 --> 00:24:10,752
Dinner's on me.

446
00:24:11,272 --> 00:24:12,832
I'm paying out of my own pocket.

447
00:24:15,393 --> 00:24:16,032
Okay, Uncle.

448
00:24:16,032 --> 00:24:19,673
You earned money in Wenzhou.
You've worked hard.

449
00:24:21,032 --> 00:24:21,552
Uncle.

450
00:24:22,873 --> 00:24:24,272
You've got great foresight.

451
00:24:25,352 --> 00:24:29,032
As soon as I arrived in Wenzhou,
the manufacturers were all over me.

452
00:24:30,032 --> 00:24:32,233
I contacted a buddy
at a construction site

453
00:24:33,112 --> 00:24:34,473
and bought the whole lot.

454
00:24:35,112 --> 00:24:36,473
Bought at 2000, sold at 20,000.

455
00:24:37,592 --> 00:24:40,713
Guess how much we made from this deal?

456
00:24:41,272 --> 00:24:41,772
How much?

457
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:43,993
You'll be shocked.

458
00:24:45,393 --> 00:24:46,233
Six hundred thousand.

459
00:24:49,032 --> 00:24:50,592
You're really something.

460
00:24:51,233 --> 00:24:53,032
You were born to make money.

461
00:24:54,112 --> 00:24:54,913
Come on, drink.

462
00:24:54,913 --> 00:24:56,873
All thanks to your guidance.

463
00:24:59,072 --> 00:25:01,913
But Uncle, I can't keep all this money.

464
00:25:02,352 --> 00:25:04,792
By rights, I should give you 30%.

465
00:25:05,433 --> 00:25:06,792
But since you're my uncle,

466
00:25:07,352 --> 00:25:09,233
let's split the money fifty-fifty.

467
00:25:10,072 --> 00:25:12,393
I admire you
more than anyone else in my life.

468
00:25:12,913 --> 00:25:15,832
You're always
forward-looking and strategic.

469
00:25:16,993 --> 00:25:18,112
Come on, Situan.

470
00:25:19,153 --> 00:25:20,032
A toast to you.

471
00:25:21,752 --> 00:25:23,352
You're like a real uncle to me.

472
00:25:27,512 --> 00:25:30,032
You've done so well all these years.

473
00:25:30,352 --> 00:25:31,153
It all makes sense.

474
00:25:32,272 --> 00:25:33,673
You're so generous.

475
00:25:34,473 --> 00:25:35,312
I'm impressed.

476
00:25:36,112 --> 00:25:36,752
Right, Uncle.

477
00:25:37,393 --> 00:25:38,673
How are you going to spend

478
00:25:39,352 --> 00:25:40,072
so much money?

479
00:25:41,792 --> 00:25:43,352
I have a lot of expenses.

480
00:25:43,352 --> 00:25:45,633
Look, that pathetic little stall of mine

481
00:25:45,633 --> 00:25:47,233
earns next to nothing each year.

482
00:25:47,792 --> 00:25:51,272
How many years would it take
for me to earn this much?

483
00:25:51,272 --> 00:25:52,153
Forget the stall.

484
00:25:53,112 --> 00:25:53,913
You're asking me?

485
00:25:54,832 --> 00:25:55,673
What about you?

486
00:25:58,112 --> 00:25:59,032
I don't know either.

487
00:25:59,673 --> 00:26:00,993
Here's an idea.

488
00:26:02,873 --> 00:26:04,673
Why don't you fix that stage?

489
00:26:04,673 --> 00:26:05,592
What stage?

490
00:26:06,233 --> 00:26:07,032
Xiangyang Commune.

491
00:26:07,433 --> 00:26:08,832
The one that collapsed.

492
00:26:11,112 --> 00:26:13,072
Qin'e doesn't sing anymore. Why bother?

493
00:26:14,193 --> 00:26:14,832
Just fix it.

494
00:26:15,393 --> 00:26:16,993
Once it's fixed, she can sing.

495
00:26:17,592 --> 00:26:19,233
Even if she doesn't, others can sing.

496
00:26:24,608 --> 00:26:28,953
(Qinqiang Opera Trainee Class
New Student Admission List)

497
00:26:28,953 --> 00:26:30,272
I got in.

498
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:37,792
(Song Yu)

499
00:26:38,633 --> 00:26:40,512
I got in, Auntie.

500
00:26:41,713 --> 00:26:42,592
I got in.

501
00:26:42,592 --> 00:26:43,953
I can sing opera now.

502
00:26:45,112 --> 00:26:45,993
Uncle Hu.

503
00:26:47,393 --> 00:26:48,233
Uncle Hu.

504
00:26:48,873 --> 00:26:49,673
I got in.

505
00:26:49,953 --> 00:26:50,633
You got in?

506
00:26:51,153 --> 00:26:52,993
My name and my examinee number

507
00:26:52,993 --> 00:26:55,193
are on that list.

508
00:26:55,433 --> 00:26:56,592
That's great.

509
00:26:57,993 --> 00:26:59,713
You have a lot to learn from your aunt.

510
00:27:00,433 --> 00:27:02,272
Try to surpass her.

511
00:27:02,688 --> 00:27:04,112
That'll take ten years of practice.

512
00:27:04,112 --> 00:27:04,953
I'll be waiting.

513
00:27:05,832 --> 00:27:07,193
I can't compare to you.

514
00:27:07,752 --> 00:27:09,072
I made ribs this morning.

515
00:27:09,072 --> 00:27:10,713
Song Yu wanted some, so I made extra.

516
00:27:11,233 --> 00:27:13,032
I had some. They're amazing.

517
00:27:13,032 --> 00:27:14,473
You and Aunt Hua should try some.

518
00:27:14,473 --> 00:27:16,193
Consider it a celebration for me.

519
00:27:16,713 --> 00:27:18,193
Alright, you got in.

520
00:27:18,713 --> 00:27:20,792
When should we tell your dad?

521
00:27:21,633 --> 00:27:24,072
That'll fulfill the promise
I made to him.

522
00:27:44,792 --> 00:27:45,433
Dad.

523
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:50,112
I got into
the provincial troupe's trainee class.

524
00:27:50,112 --> 00:27:50,993
(Loving Father, Song Guangzu)

525
00:27:50,993 --> 00:27:51,913
Uncle Hu said

526
00:27:52,592 --> 00:27:55,272
he fulfilled his promise to you,
so you can rest in peace.

527
00:27:57,153 --> 00:27:58,312
I've almost fulfilled

528
00:27:59,713 --> 00:28:00,673
my promise to you.

529
00:28:04,873 --> 00:28:05,873
I will soon

530
00:28:07,873 --> 00:28:10,193
become the most beautiful girl

531
00:28:11,752 --> 00:28:12,792
by going on stage.

532
00:28:22,673 --> 00:28:23,752
It's a happy day.

533
00:28:27,832 --> 00:28:28,913
How about I sing for you?

534
00:28:43,072 --> 00:28:54,552
笙ｪWest Lake is still the same笙ｪ

535
00:29:00,193 --> 00:29:07,312
笙ｪBut my haggard self笙ｪ

536
00:29:07,312 --> 00:29:08,112
(Beloved son, Liu Yi)
Yi.

537
00:29:08,993 --> 00:29:09,633
Listen.

538
00:29:11,153 --> 00:29:13,193
Your sister Song Yu is singing opera.

539
00:29:15,673 --> 00:29:17,633
You loved hanging out with her, right?

540
00:29:19,752 --> 00:29:21,473
She lives with us now.

541
00:29:23,112 --> 00:29:24,112
From now on,

542
00:29:25,393 --> 00:29:26,792
she will learn to sing opera.

543
00:29:39,808 --> 00:29:42,144
(Loving Father, Song Guangzu)

544
00:29:59,193 --> 00:29:59,913
Uncle.

545
00:30:01,193 --> 00:30:02,512
I'm Song Yu.

546
00:30:04,032 --> 00:30:05,473
I got into the provincial troupe.

547
00:30:07,552 --> 00:30:09,633
I just sang a piece for my dad.

548
00:30:11,792 --> 00:30:12,512
How about

549
00:30:14,352 --> 00:30:15,673
I sing a piece for you too?

550
00:30:21,473 --> 00:30:23,072
What kind of opera did he like?

551
00:30:24,673 --> 00:30:26,233
He liked everything I've performed.

552
00:30:26,792 --> 00:30:29,473
Which piece did he like most?

553
00:30:30,873 --> 00:30:31,832
His favorite was

554
00:30:33,713 --> 00:30:36,233
"Yang Men Nyu Jiang:
Exploring the Valley".

555
00:30:38,633 --> 00:30:40,873
Have you sung it for him alone?

556
00:30:47,296 --> 00:30:50,009
(Liu Hongbing)

557
00:30:52,633 --> 00:30:53,352
No.

558
00:30:56,193 --> 00:30:57,913
Then sing it for him.

559
00:32:19,713 --> 00:32:22,072
Custom-made for you. Do you like it?

560
00:32:25,633 --> 00:32:28,352
They say a star
must have their own costume.

561
00:32:29,713 --> 00:32:31,312
The first time I saw you,

562
00:32:32,193 --> 00:32:33,272
you were Mu Guiying.

563
00:32:34,032 --> 00:32:36,193
Then let's start with Mu Guiying.

564
00:32:38,112 --> 00:32:39,532
Take a look.

565
00:32:46,352 --> 00:32:48,913
Once we save up enough money,

566
00:32:49,592 --> 00:32:52,473
I'll get you
Li Huiniang's headdress set.

567
00:32:53,512 --> 00:32:55,433
Yang Paifeng's, Bai Yunxian's.

568
00:32:57,233 --> 00:32:59,393
Whatever you sing,
I'll get you the costume for it.

569
00:33:11,673 --> 00:33:15,433
I haven't sung for you alone, have I?

570
00:34:33,673 --> 00:34:34,592
笙ｪWind笙ｪ

571
00:34:41,673 --> 00:34:42,792
笙ｪWind笙ｪ

572
00:34:43,072 --> 00:34:44,592
笙ｪWind笙ｪ

573
00:34:48,352 --> 00:34:58,633
笙ｪThe wind howls笙ｪ

574
00:35:00,592 --> 00:35:05,913
笙ｪThe mist is thick笙ｪ

575
00:35:09,072 --> 00:35:14,512
笙ｪThe mist is thick笙ｪ

576
00:35:18,752 --> 00:35:37,713
笙ｪThe starlight is dim笙ｪ

577
00:35:56,032 --> 00:35:59,273
笙ｪHorses gallop; birds are startled笙ｪ

578
00:35:59,273 --> 00:36:03,672
笙ｪThe winding mountain road is desolate笙ｪ

579
00:36:03,672 --> 00:36:09,353
笙ｪOn the way here, the sky darkens笙ｪ

580
00:36:09,353 --> 00:36:13,672
笙ｪThe moon somehow rises笙ｪ

581
00:36:17,353 --> 00:36:22,672
笙ｪIn the east笙ｪ

582
00:36:22,672 --> 00:36:29,512
笙ｪThe wind blows笙ｪ

583
00:36:35,873 --> 00:36:37,592
(Rest if you're tired.)

584
00:36:39,273 --> 00:36:40,313
(Stay where you are)

585
00:36:40,913 --> 00:36:41,913
(if you're lost.)

586
00:36:43,712 --> 00:36:44,672
(Or turn around.)

587
00:36:46,232 --> 00:36:46,913
(I promise.)

588
00:36:47,913 --> 00:36:48,833
(When you turn around,)

589
00:36:50,672 --> 00:36:51,672
(I'll be right there.)

590
00:38:23,833 --> 00:38:24,632
Aunt Hua.

591
00:38:26,232 --> 00:38:28,873
It's alright.
I just came to sit with you.

592
00:38:34,393 --> 00:38:38,753
I haven't watched the audience
from this spot for years.

593
00:38:40,112 --> 00:38:42,512
I suddenly understood
the meaning of "a lifetime apart."

594
00:38:45,753 --> 00:38:46,873
So familiar

595
00:38:47,953 --> 00:38:49,152
and so strange.

596
00:38:52,112 --> 00:38:54,393
You want to be on stage forever, right?

597
00:38:55,353 --> 00:38:56,552
Who doesn't?

598
00:38:57,913 --> 00:39:00,393
Those who've heard applause and cheers

599
00:39:00,712 --> 00:39:01,833
want it even more.

600
00:39:04,753 --> 00:39:06,473
But what can you do?

601
00:39:07,873 --> 00:39:11,112
You're always
playing someone else on stage.

602
00:39:12,072 --> 00:39:15,313
You can only be yourself off stage.

603
00:39:28,632 --> 00:39:31,993
However brilliant the script,
it's someone else's story.

604
00:39:32,753 --> 00:39:35,833
But your life is yours to live.

605
00:39:37,152 --> 00:39:38,273
Since you'll sing,

606
00:39:39,393 --> 00:39:40,833
you must sing it beautifully.

607
00:39:41,913 --> 00:39:42,592
Right?

608
00:40:03,753 --> 00:40:04,608
Don't be afraid.

609
00:40:29,512 --> 00:40:30,368
Don't be afraid.

610
00:40:31,552 --> 00:40:32,592
It's your uncle.

611
00:41:32,953 --> 00:41:33,873
Be the lead.

612
00:42:07,040 --> 00:42:10,144
(Qinqiang Opera Theater
Personnel Transfer Application Form)

613
00:42:15,072 --> 00:42:15,833
Qin'e.

614
00:42:16,913 --> 00:42:18,032
Is this real?

615
00:42:22,512 --> 00:42:23,313
Come on, pinch me.

616
00:42:23,313 --> 00:42:24,632
Let me see if it hurts.

617
00:42:25,313 --> 00:42:26,232
It will hurt.

618
00:42:27,433 --> 00:42:28,152
This is real.

619
00:42:36,552 --> 00:42:37,712
Are you sure?

620
00:42:47,032 --> 00:42:47,873
Qin'e.

621
00:42:50,032 --> 00:42:53,672
I've always thought
I was a lousy troupe leader,

622
00:42:55,473 --> 00:42:57,993
barely holding this troupe together.

623
00:42:58,353 --> 00:43:00,353
But seeing this paper of yours today,

624
00:43:01,192 --> 00:43:04,072
I finally feel like
I can stand tall for once.

625
00:43:05,242 --> 00:43:06,944
(Preview)

626
00:43:09,210 --> 00:43:10,891
I have been tough my whole life.

627
00:43:11,010 --> 00:43:11,971
Stay out of my business.

628
00:43:12,610 --> 00:43:13,530
When you're in trouble,

629
00:43:13,971 --> 00:43:15,731
you know you can count on me.

630
00:43:15,811 --> 00:43:17,570
Is the training a bit too tough?

631
00:43:17,931 --> 00:43:19,530
After all, she's not young anymore.

632
00:43:19,891 --> 00:43:20,690
Perform You Xi Hu.

633
00:43:20,811 --> 00:43:23,411
Let's finish that opera
we couldn't finish

634
00:43:23,731 --> 00:43:24,451
five years ago.

635
00:43:25,251 --> 00:43:27,050
The Lakeside Tour scene, get ready.

636
00:43:27,050 --> 00:43:28,331
Get on standby.

637
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
笙ｪWhen I woke up and turned back笙ｪ

638
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
笙ｪI wasn't sure where to go笙ｪ

639
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
笙ｪWe met and brushed past笙ｪ

640
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
笙ｪYour shadow drifted out of sight笙ｪ

641
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
笙ｪThe stove fire blazed in my dream笙ｪ

642
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
笙ｪLit up the tracks of pearly tears笙ｪ

643
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
笙ｪIn my dream, water sleeves flew笙ｪ

644
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
笙ｪHiding a lifetime of love笙ｪ

645
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
笙ｪThe Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage笙ｪ

646
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
笙ｪSpring water brewed strong wine笙ｪ

647
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
笙ｪSheep moved through the valley笙ｪ

648
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
笙ｪIt felt like a promise
from another life笙ｪ

649
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
笙ｪWhen I woke up and turned back笙ｪ

650
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
笙ｪI wasn't sure where to go笙ｪ

651
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
笙ｪIf I chose again, I'd still roam笙ｪ

652
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
笙ｪAll over this sunlit plateau笙ｪ

653
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
笙ｪThe dream ends; the curtain falls笙ｪ

654
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
笙ｪMoonlight washes off this stage makeup笙ｪ

655
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
笙ｪThe one in the mirror wears gray hair笙ｪ

656
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
笙ｪAlready sang all my joy and sorrow笙ｪ

657
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
笙ｪAlready shouted across Qinchuan Plain笙ｪ
